==English==
=== Etymology 1 ===
Diminutive of ''[[truck]] a [[wheel]]'' or from the kindred Latin ''[[trochlea]]'' "a block, sheaf containing one or more pulleys"

=== Noun ===
'''truckle'''
# a small [[wheel]]; a [[caster]]

=== Etymology 2 ===
From truckle in [[truckle-bed]], in allusion to the fact that the truckle-bed on which the pupil slept was rolled under the large bed of the master.

=== Intransitive Verb ===
'''truckle'''
# to [[act]] in a [[submissive]] [[manner]]; to submit to a [[superior]]